intro: Gynaphanes australis, commonly known as the Australian gynaphane, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Myrtaceae, which includes eucalyptus and tea trees. The plant is characterized by its small, white to pale yellow flowers that bloom in clusters. Its leaves are narrow and evergreen, often with a slight aromatic scent. Gynaphanes australis is typically found in coastal areas and sandy soils, thriving in well-drained environments.
